[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3]Restores the missing arrow icons on the craft window — left/right on the quantity buttons, and the up/down glyph on the expand/collapse toggle inside multiquality recipes (game update on 11 April 2026 shipped without the assets...)[/size]
[*][size=3]Smooths out player movement with physics interpolation (no more grid-snapping judder).[/size]
[*][size=3]Adds a tunable footprint cap and fixes footprints popping out of existence instead of fading.[/size]
[*][size=3]Optional toggles to keep the game running while the window is unfocused and to mute its audio while unfocused.[/size]
[*][size=3]Silently ignores a handful of harmless vanilla exceptions that previously could spam the log or crash on edge-case saves.[/size]
[*][size=3]Keeps timber and ore stockpiles visible when another mod raises their capacity — the pile stays drawn as "full" past the usual 10-item limit instead of vanishing.[/size]
[*][size=3]More fixes will be added over time as small vanilla bugs are found.[/size]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

